description:
Carlos is passionate about the teaching case method. He is co-author of more than 25 of them in the areas of finance, strategy, operations, and sustainability. Some of them have been included in the case databases of prestigious business schools such as Harvard, Michigan, and IESE.

He has oriented his research towards the impact of social, environmental, and corporate governance (ESG) information on financial markets. He has also carried out studies on entrepreneurial financing in contexts with institutional voids.

His research has been presented at prestigious conferences such as the Alliance for Research on Corporate Sustainability (MIT, USA) doctoral colloquium, the specialized conference “From Start-up to Scale-up” of the Academy of Management (University of Tel-Aviv, Israel ), the Third Conference on Entrepreneurial Finance (Politecnico di Milano, Italy) and the Annual Congress of the European Accounting Association (Valencia, Spain).

Carlos is the co-author of five papers in peer-reviewed scientific journals and two book chapters (published by Edward Elgar and World Scientific Publishing). His research has been cited by the International Integrated Reporting Council in white papers for institutional investors. Additionally, he has been an occasional reviewer for various academic journals.

Sobresale en la construcción de marcas con propósito, diseño y descubrimiento de consumer insights, planning y storytelling de marcas, estrategia digital, diseño de research y consulting. Especialista en Hispanic and Latino markets.

Su constante interés por fortalecer el impacto social de las marcas la ha llevado a ser parte y dirigir esfuerzos de trascendencia en temas como malnutrición infantil, abuso contra la mujer y la niñez, prevención de violencia intrafamiliar entre otros temas. Así también ha formado parte de equipos de asesoría en estrategia de comunicación para partidos políticos y proyectos ciudadanos emergentes.

Es conferencista activa, creadora de talleres, charlas y seminarios a nivel nacional e internacional, en diversas plataformas y universidades. Es así como mantiene viva su pasión por enseñar y formar talento estratégico.

Lideró el departamento más grande de planning integrado del país, además de ser nombrada Black Belt en herramientas estratégicas de la red global y dirigir el área de Consulting en El Salvador y proyectos para CA.

Actiz para cine y televisión.

description:
Nabyl Charania is most passionate about leaving a positive, generational, world-changing legacy. He chases this higher aspiration through a personal Massive Transformative Purpose (MTP) he has set and challenged himself to achieve in his lifetime: Create incorruptible prosperity and abundant ecosystems for all across the universe.

Nabyl draws inspiration for his MTP from the ethical framework of the Aga Khan Development Network (AKDN) and the mission of the XPRIZE Foundation. As a legacy donor, he supports the AKDN’s fundamental objective to improve the quality of human life through a variety of agencies working in the fields of economic development, education, healthcare, and cultural enrichment. As a member of the XPRIZE Vision Circle, Nabyl joins Larry Page, Sergey Brin, Ratan Tata, and other global business leaders to contribute thought leadership and funds for XPRIZE’s large-scale global incentive competitions that crowdsource solutions to the world’s grand challenges. Nabyl is also fascinated by space, and is excited to pursue space travel and other space projects that line up with his MTP.

Nabyl is a serial entrepreneur with multiple exits, and has seeded several successful companies as well as crypto funds with outstanding returns. He founded Rokk3r, one of the first company builders globally that over the years has evolved into a strategic holding company focussed on exponential technology companies. He is Co-Founder, Fund Sponsor and Curator at Meta4 Capital, where he combines his entrepreneurial track record with his passions for art, music, culture and of course sneakers.

Nabyl grew up in Kenya’s capital city of Nairobi where seeing his dad tinkering with electronics, and his neighbors and community working together to solve any problem no matter how big or small, are his earliest memories of technology and the power of human potential.
headline: Vision Circle at XPRIZE :: Co-Founder at Meta4Capital :: Chairman at Rokk3r :: Founding Partner Rokk3r Fuel ExO

description:
Hey there! I'm Carlos, a young business professional native from El Salvador. I'm currently pursuing my MBA at Simon Fraser University in Vancouver, Canada. I graduated Summa Cum Laude from John Brown University (Arkansas, USA) in May 2016 with a Bachelor of Arts in International Business, a Bachelor of Science in Marketing and Business Administration, and a minor in Leadership. I was recognized as the Highest-Ranking Graduate from the Soderquist College of Business (2016). I have been a scholarship recipient from: Beedie Family Graduate Scholarship (2020), Peter Legge Graduate Volunteer Leadership Award (2020), Walton International Scholarship Program (2012-2016), U.S. Department of State - Youth Ambassadors (2011), and Programa Oportunidades by Gloria de Kriete Foundation (2009-2011).

Upon graduating from college, I returned to my home country to work as a Marketing Analyst for Amway Central America and was promoted in 2018 to Sales Project Manager in Amway Latin America. I believe we all have a responsibility to leave a better world for the future generations, hence I have always been involved in projects and organizations (such as ENACTUS and the Youth Council for the U.S. Embassy in El Salvador) aligned to my passions - entrepreneurship, small business development, and youth empowerment – as part of my giving back philosophy. I served as the Director of the 2016 Alumni Engagement Innovation Fund winning project for El Salvador, “Jóvenes Pioneros” for five years. An organization born out of a $25K grant by the U.S. Department of State that promotes youth entrepreneurship through an innovative business curriculum designed for high school students. In February 2020, I was recognized as one of twenty “Influential Youth from the Republic of El Salvador” for my volunteering endeavors.

In September 2020, I began my MBA studies online - given mobility restrictions - while I also joined local Salvadoran politics and ran for Congress as one of the youngest candidates for El Salvador's February 28, 2021 elections. Shortly after my participation, I was named National Youth Coordinator for the up-and-coming political party, Nuestro Tiempo on April 2021.

My future plans include advancing my professional career in business, continue contributing to the development of sustainable social impact projects, and continue my involvement in Salvadoran politics.

Feel free to reach out to me at carlose.lopezs94@gmail.com!

description:
Daniel Runde is a Senior Vice President at the Center for Strategic and International Studies and holds the William A. Schreyer Chair in Global Analysis, where he focuses on the role of using soft power to shape the future. A global thought leader, Mr. Runde has advised a number of governments including the United States, Japan, Denmark, Korea as well as the World Bank and the United Nations. He has testified before the U.S. Congress, and the Australian and Canadian parliaments.

In April 2018, Mr. Runde was named the Chair of the Advisory Committee for Voluntary Foreign Assistance, the Federal Advisory Committee that advises the Administrator of the US Agency for International Development and the broader federal government on international development issues.

Prior to coming to CSIS, Mr. Runde held senior roles and led organization change initiatives and built strategic partnerships at the World Bank Group and the US Agency for International Development. Mr. Runde is an Opinions Contributor at Thehill.com. He blogs occasionally at "Elephants in the Room" at ForeignPolicy.com. He writes and speaks extensively on global development issues. He was a member of the World Economic Forum Global Agenda Council for the United States. He currently serves on the board of the International Foundation for Electoral Systems (IFES) and the Ashesi University Foundation board, a Ghanaian university.

He has been featured in Inc Magazine's 30 under 30 and Inc 5000. He is also President of Colabora Holdings, a group of companies based in El Salvador that develops businesses within the sharing economy; Point, the first business center and coworking exclusively for entrepreneurs and LIVE the first co-living facility in El Salvador.
Alfredo is Brand Ambassador for El Salvador as Entrepreneur since 2017, he is also part of the Aspen Global Leadership Network and CALI Fellow.
He has been part of YEC and YPO, additionally Alfredo has been involved in The Chamber of Commerce as part of the board of directors from 2016 to 2019.
Alfredo in President of Fundacion Colabora, the group's non profit whose main goal is to promote entrepreneurship in El Salvador via different programs, including an Angel Investment fund.

Creadora de la metodología Social Impact Planning y parte del equipo de Ogilvy Consulting para la región. Con más de 15 años de experiencia en diversos rubros y mercados. U.S. citizen and fully bilingual.

Sobresale en la construcción de marcas con propósito, diseño y descubrimiento de consumer insights, planning y storytelling de marcas, estrategia digital, diseño de research y consulting. Especialista en Hispanic and Latino markets.

Amplia experiencia como creativa y planner en diversas agencias reconocidas de la región. Trabajando para marcas líderes locales y regionales con las que ha ganado 5 Effies, además de otros premios creativos locales y centroamericanos.

Su constante interés por fortalecer el impacto social de las marcas la ha llevado a ser parte y dirigir esfuerzos de trascendencia en temas como malnutrición infantil, abuso contra la mujer y la niñez, prevención de violencia intrafamiliar entre otros temas. Lo que la lleva a fundar la innovadora iniciativa Social Impact Planning que replantean el RSE con una mirada más estratégica y creativa, alineada a la construcción de marcas con propósito. Así también ha formado parte de equipos de asesoría en estrategia de comunicación para partidos políticos y proyectos ciudadanos emergentes.

Es conferencista activa, creadora de talleres, charlas y seminarios a nivel nacional e internacional, en diversas plataformas y universidades. Es así como mantiene viva su pasión por enseñar y formar talento estratégico.

Lideró el departamento más grande de planning integrado del país, además de ser nombrada Black Belt en herramientas estratégicas de la red global y dirigir el área de Consulting en El Salvador y proyectos para CA.

Actiz para cine y televisión.
